# Moth(er):Br+AI+n — .dockerignore for reference deployment (S6-DB-5).
#
# Goal: send the smallest possible context to the Docker daemon. Anything
# not needed to compile the `motherbrain` binary belongs here.
#
# Honesty: a few of these exclusions (tests, archive) are for context
# size — the builder runs `cargo build --release -p motherbrain-cli`
# which doesn't need test sources or archived starter kits.

# --- Build outputs ---
# Cargo's `target/` can be multi-GB. Never ship it into the build context.
**/target/
target/

# --- Git + local tooling ---
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# --- Editor / OS noise ---
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Runtime CMDB artifacts ---
# These are produced by sensory tools at runtime, not part of the source
# tree. Keeping them out of the image prevents stale health data from
# leaking into the deployment layer.
.claude/*-cmdb.json
.claude/scheduled-tasks.db
.claude/command-history.db
.claude/conversation.db

# --- Docs / reference material the binary doesn't need ---
# The binary produces its output on stdout; it doesn't read these at run.
whitepaper/
docs/
README.md
CLAUDE.md
*.md

# --- Archived / out-of-scope directories ---
starter-kit/
sdk-python/
archive/

# --- Containerisation artifacts ---
# Don't re-ship docker files into themselves; makes layer diffs noisier
# and wastes context.
Dockerfile
docker-compose.yml
.dockerignore

# --- Example project roots (the deployment's fixtures) ---
# These are mounted into the container at `/brain` at run time, not baked
# into the image. Excluding them keeps the image small and prevents the
# example fixture from ever leaking into a production build.
motherbrain-local-project/
motherbrain-external-project/

# --- Verification scripts (host-side only) ---
scripts/
.verify-tmp/
